no-octal.description:
Description

The rule disallows octal literals.

If ESLint parses code in strict mode, the parser (instead of this rule) reports the error.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-octal: "error"*/

const num = 071;
const result = 5 + 07;

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-octal: "error"*/

const num  = "071";
